  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Integrated Multi-sector Emergency and Recovery for IDPs and Host Communities in North Darfur</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Relief International (RI) will provide quality multi-sectoral emergency lifesaving and recovery services to conflict- and natural disaster-affected IDPs and host-communities in Saraf Umrah and Malha localities in North Darfur. These services include improved management treatment, and prevention of acute malnutrition using a community-based approach integrated with the provision of essential primary health care and WASH services whilst factoring in protection mainstreaming within the sectors and emergency response for any emergencies as a result of flood and outbreaks that might arise. The above-integrated services will be delivered through 10 already-established integrated health and nutrition facilities and their surrounding catchment populations, building on RI&#x2019;s existing work in the target locations. RI will use needs assessments, report analysis, routine monitoring, post distribution monitoring and end line assessments to measure the impact of this project on vulnerable populations including women and girls, severely and moderately malnourished children under five, and pregnant and lactating women (PLW). The proposed project was designed based on the findings of RI&#x2019;s needs assessment (annexed) that identified major gaps and acute needs in the project area particularly nutrition, health, WASH and protection. The dire humanitarian situation is further exacerbated by the ongoing economic crisis, the COVID-19 pandemic as well as limited available services and investments in the construction and rehabilitation of facilities. As these factors continue to occur, urgent lifesaving intervention will be required to reduce excess morbidity and mortality among the affected communities. Therefore, RI will work to increase accessibility, quality and coordination of Nutrition, Health, WASH services and build long-term capacity for preventing and addressing acute malnutrition at all levels in the targeted communities in Saraf Umrah and Malha in North Darfur.</narrative>
  </description>
